<h1>How Yediyurappa is an exception to BJP rule </h1>
<pre>
Karnataka Bengaluru News July 22 Highlights: Amid continued speculation of leadership change 
in Karnataka, a Lingayat seer, Sri Sangana Basava Swami of Kottur Veerashaiva Shivayoga Mandir,
 Wednesday alleged “an RSS conspiracy” behind the plans to remove Chief Minister BS Yediyurappa.
  Speaking to reporters in Hospet, Sri Basava Swami said “RSS is a caste-based organisation” and has no 
  “liberal-minded” leaders.
